The course gives an overview of the following themes: structure of the cover article, main problems with writing the cover article;  main expectations and demands regarding the cover article. The student is expected to write the first draft of their cover article, present and discuss about it in the seminar and act as an opponent for the fellow student's cover article or monograph.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to assist doctoral students in writing the "cover articles" of their dissertation or helping them wrap up their monographs.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course a doctoral student is able to write and review the "cover article" of their dissertation or wrap up their monograph.
